WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:17.751 --> 00:00:22.480
We're driving the new Peugeot 208,
successor of the Peugeot 207.

00:00:22.481 --> 00:00:27.045
The car might not sound very exciting, but
it may turn out more fun than you imagine.

00:00:27.046 --> 00:00:34.516
Whilst designing this car Peugeot tried to downsize this
car, specifically on terms of his exterior sizes and weight.

00:00:34.517 --> 00:00:39.629
In contrast to all other brands, who make their cars
bigger in order to generate more space,...

00:00:39.630 --> 00:00:44.692
... Peugeot wanted to make the car smaller
but still create more interior space.

00:00:44.693 --> 00:00:45.900
They achieved to do so.

00:00:45.901 --> 00:00:54.076
The 208 is much lighter than the 207, it's been reduced by 170 kg's (374 lbs)
with some versions and an average of 110 kg (242 lbs) on all versions.

00:00:54.077 --> 00:01:00.218
The lose in weight is noticeable, the steering
is much more joyful than with the previous version.

00:01:00.219 --> 00:01:05.597
This is also induced by the small steering wheel, something
Peugeot introduced with a reason.

00:01:05.598 --> 00:01:11.873
They wanted to place the instruments a little higher, which resulted
in the fact that you can't see them because of the steering wheel.

00:01:11.874 --> 00:01:13.643
That's why they reduced the size of the steering wheel.

00:01:13.644 --> 00:01:20.621
But it also contributes to the fun of driving because the wheel is
smaller, more sporty and the steering is more stern.

00:01:20.622 --> 00:01:27.128
This gives you feeling you can really cut corners
and play with the car.

00:01:27.129 --> 00:01:37.041
The reduction in size therefore enhanced the pleasure of
driving and the feeling of involvement in driving this car.

00:01:37.042 --> 00:01:42.549
My foreign colleagues clearly did the same thing.

00:01:42.550 --> 00:01:51.118
It has driven just under 3000 km (1900 miles) and
has all sorts of noises and rattles.

00:01:52.053 --> 00:01:56.490
Might be the newness of the car,
but it's rather annoying.

00:01:56.491 --> 00:01:58.309
Let put it at rather French.

00:02:10.098 --> 00:02:13.600
We're driving a 1.6 E HDi, a diesel.

00:02:14.087 --> 00:02:16.572
